Text.SourceString: My day is great, thank you for asking, <PlayerName>$player</>. How are you today?//<portrait=happy>Have you checked out my furniture store?
No time like the present, I always say. Heh heh!
I’m not one to garden, but it would be nice to rely less on <NpcName>Sam</> for fresh fruits.
We plant small vegetables and herbs, but our garden is not big enough to grow fruits.
I’m not one to garden, but it would be nice to rely less on <NpcName>Sam</> for fresh fruits.
We plant small vegetables and herbs, but our garden is not big enough to grow fruits.
It would be nice to have a large farm like yours, but then taking care of it must take a lot of time.
Now that I think about it, I don’t think I have the time for it.
I like to stretch my legs after work and usually end up at Fishensips.
Fun finds a way, huh?
After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things that I learned from my childhood.
After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things that I learned from my childhood.
Where I am from, there are plenty of small islands too. Just like in here.
My nephew, <NpcName>Surya</>, is new in town. He studied the ocean and is currently working for <NPCName>Ling</>.
You've met him, right? He is about your age, I believe.

How is the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build up a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops. It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. Because you can grow anything all year round in it.
The soil here is very rich. When I take <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest, we always seem to stumble upon a new plant type.
How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Is the farm going okay?
I'm teaching <NpcName>Archie</> how to fish. That boy is talented, but there is definitely room for improvement.
My wife is a great cook. If she weren’t a carpenter, she would probably be a chef… A big name one, I’m sure.
I have no doubt that if she opened a restaurant, she would have many loyal customers.//<portrait=happy>And one of them would be me. Heh heh.
<NpcName>Dinda</> loves gardening, flower bouquet, salad, and pearls. I honestly don’t think she hates anything.
Oh! She hates avocado, ice cream, and mayonnaise.//Weird texture... To be frank, I’m no fan of mayonnaise, either. It’s rather nasty.
This job comes with the territory. I threw my back out one time and had to be on bed rest for the rest of the year.
I can still feel a pinch a bit when I stretch a particular position. But don’t worry though I’m fine. Thanks.
We are open 'til 5pm today.
Sunday is our short day. We are only open until 1ish.
There are fascinating people on TV. I’m lost for words sometimes.
I saw a grown man throw a bucket full of ice onto himself, outside, in the Winter weather. Why?
You can make a bouquet of flowers yourself. You just need to get the recipe from <NpcName>Dinda</> or <NpcName>Ben</>. The key is to get to know them a little, and they will probably teach you.
A new day is here, and the birds are singing. What more can we ask for.
Indeed. I did wake up in a very good mood. What gives?
The library is a place full of information. And you know what they say about knowledge!
That it’s a powerful thing!

How is the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build up a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops.//It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. Because you can grow anything all year round in it.
Remember to take a rest, <PlayerName>$player</>. Wealth isn’t everything.
You're always welcome to our house for dinner. I know it’s hard to be away from family sometimes.
I like working outdoor when it isn't raining.
I get too busy during the week. I can only make it down to yoga classes on Saturdays.
It’s not like they have yoga class any other day, anyway.
My brother and I used to go fishing every day on Summer break. We would disappear the whole day until the sun sets.
Do you get your woods from the forest? I go there too because it’s the closest area to the house.//There are plenty of areas that have woods around the island, though, if you need more.
<NpcName>Archie</> is fine, though sometimes he would have a picky-eating period. But what kid doesn’t, right?
We don’t sell our woods. We just don’t have the space to store that kind of inventory.
If you want to upgrade your cabin or build something, you would need to supply the materials.
<NpcName>Archie</> is fine, though sometimes he would have a picky-eating period. But what kid doesn’t, right?
Do you get your woods from the forest? I go there too because it’s the closest area to the house.//There are plenty of areas that have woods around the island, though, if you need more.
It’s probably not the healthiest to cut wood indoors, especially with the debris and all flying around.
I make it a habit to come down to the town on the weekend for some yoga.
Let’s face it, it's an excellent excuse to see the islanders too.
Do you get your woods from the forest? I go there too because it’s the closest area to the house.//There are plenty of areas that have woods around the island, though, if you need more.
I get too busy during the week. I can only make it down to yoga classes on Saturdays.
It’s probably not the healthiest to cut wood indoors, especially with the debris and all flying around.
It’s best to do it outside and do the easy woodwork indoor.
I’m thinking of taking <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest tomorrow after school.
The lake is too far from our house. I think by the time we fish there and back, it would be close to midnight.
Looking fresh there, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look like you got in some serious farming today.
It always makes me feel good after a whole day of hard work. It's great to feel productive!
My work needs me to have a lot of energy every day. So every morning, I make sure to have a big breakfast to start the day with.
You can see our available projects at the cash register. We keep the catalog there.
You can buy the wall clocks if you'd like. They're for sale.//Talk to <NpcName>Dinda</> for more information though, she deals with the sales.
It feels good to work with your hands, doesn’t it? You're a farmer, <PlayerName>$player</>, you get it.
We are lucky, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not everyone can do what we do.//Don’t be too hard on yourself, okay.
It feels good to work with your hands, doesn’t it? You're a farmer, <PlayerName>$player</>, you get it.
We are lucky, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not everyone can do what we do.//Don’t be too hard on yourself, okay.
My work needs me to have a lot of energy every day.//So every morning, I make sure to have a big breakfast to start the day with.
I'm not trying to be difficult, but I can’t start working on a large project without payment.
Well, large projects are more like upgrading a house or building a coop. I don’t consider a shipping bin or a chair, a large project.
The thing with <NpcName>Archie</> is that if one of his friends is sick, the whole class would probably be sick. Then, do you know who gets sick after that?
Their parents, which includes me.
There is so much that we can pass on to our children. The little thing that we, the parents, do can become their habit.
There are simple crafts that you can make yourself to improve your farm.
We sell some of these blueprints if you would like to try it.
The warmer weather is ahead. Are you planting any berries this Summer?
<NpcName>Surya</> is my brother, <NpcName>Suparmo</>'s, oldest son.
He's a smart one, you can just tell.
I’m going to focus on work today and have a quiet evening with a plate of banana fritters.
I've spent a lot of time working outdoors this Summer.
As a farmer, you must spend a lot of your time outdoor too, I figure.//Well, at least for us, fresh air isn’t a problem. Heh heh
The evenings have started to cool off a bit.
I think the Fall weather is coming.
It's incredibly hot this year, I tell ya.
It was much colder last year.
Are you planting melons this year? It's a popular fruit in our household.
I might go down to Sam's and see if he's got any melons to sell.//You know, to score that extra brownie points with <NpcName>Dinda</>.
What is it about Summer that is making people productive?//I woke up earlier than usual and got way more things done during the day.
I feel incredibly old now that I start bragging about waking up early. Heh heh.
I’m a bit busier than usual.
With the Harvest Festival coming up, I have to make sure all the booths are ready to use and fix the broken parts.
The mayor will have one empty booth for you to use if you decide to join in, <PlayerName>$player</>. I will make sure it’s nice and sturdy.
I’m relieved that the Harvest Festival ended without incident.//I’m always worried that a booth might break or something.
I know it’s irrational, but I can’t help it sometimes.
I make sure to buy a few extra pumpkins for <NpcName>Archie</> and me to carve.//<portrait=happy>Now that the weather is nice, we just chill around the house and carve.
I think this pumpkin carving thing will be a tradition in our family.//I can see it being passed down to generations.

To be frank, I don’t care much about how our pumpkins look when I carve with <NpcName>Archie</>.//<portrait=happy>I just know that it’s something that he's always looking forward to every year, and it's become a tradition.
Do you have a lot of pumpkins on your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I’m sure your farm looks excellent! I have to go there and see it sometimes.

One of these days, I will need to check on the community center and the lab to prepare them for Winter.//You know, just a quick inspection to make sure that the heater is working, no leaks on the roofs, and whatnot.
Have you tried to make some crafts like scarecrows? They can be very helpful in your farm.
I’m not going to focus much on work today. It’s cold, and I can use some downtime.
Our herb plants wilted. None of them can survive the Winter snow.
I don’t mind working on a project in the Winter. Keeping busy warms me up.
Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.
Ah, I’m going to miss the snow.
The snow may be melting soon, but the weather will still be chilly for at least the first week.
<NPCName>Dinda</> and I used to live in Indonesia. We fell in love with the quiet, peaceful life on the island!
I still try to make it home every now and again to visit family.

I can’t imagine a better life than working with my wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>.//<portrait=happy>She’s like my varnish – I’m just not complete without her.//<portrait=happy>Look at me all <Italic>love-dovey</>! Heh heh!
My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, and <NPCName>Valentina</> get along really well!//<NPCName>Valentina</> is <NPCName>Rafael</>'s niece, you know, and we see them all the time.
I love watching them play together.
People are so interesting, aren’t they? Everyone has a story!
I’ve gotten really good at making chairs over the years.
My wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>, keeps a garden. It’s small, but the herbs she grows are delicious.
If I were you, I’d hope she doesn’t expand.//<portrait=happy>She’d put you out of business!
I made a little table for <NPCName>Archie</> when he was a toddler.//He loved it!
We use it for storage now, but looking at it still brings back happy memories.
I love stepping into the workshop in the morning. It’s my happy place.
<NPCName>Dinda</> and I actually knew each other in grade school! Can you believe it?
I took <NPCName>Archie</> up to the old lighthouse last weekend.//<portrait=happy>He spent all his time mermaid-watching.//<portrait=annoyed>He didn’t see any.
If there’s one rule of woodworking, it’s this: Respect the saw.
See how I still have all my fingers? That’s because I take the rule seriously.
Hey there, <PlayerName>$player</>! Working hard or hardly working?
Working hard, I bet. Sorry, I didn’t mean to offend you.
I always keep my tools handy. You’d be surprised how often you need a screwdriver.
You must have quite the green thumb, <PlayerName>$player</>!
You should probably stop by the clinic to get that checked out.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! I crack me up.
Can’t stop to talk today. Just got a huge order!
It’s from an independent video rental store on the mainland.//I know, how quaint! I think they still have movies on VHS.
They want new shelving for their store, but the dimensions are odd.//A few centimeters under industry-standard, rounded corners…
No problem for me, of course! I run a custom shop, you know, and I can make shelving to any specifications. It’s my passion.
But like I said, can’t really talk today…
I’ve been woodworking ever since I was young.//I just did it for fun, but I never thought I could turn my hobby into a career.
But people seem to love the work I do. I feel so blessed!
I’ve been woodworking ever since I was young.//I just did it for fun, but I never thought I could turn my hobby into a career.
But people seem to love the work I do. I feel so blessed!
<NPCName>Dinda</> and I have been on Coral Island for…wow, has it been ten years already?//Gosh, must've been more!
Time flies when you’re having fun!
<NPCName>Bree</> and <NPCName>Walter</> are the other farmers in town.//They run the vineyard.
You should go introduce yourself if you haven’t already.
You’re a busy little bee, aren’t you? Well, don’t let me get in your way!
Have you met my nephew yet? <NPCName>Surya</>? He’s a lovely fellow!//You should stop by the lab and say hello.
<NPCName>Rafael Sanchez</> doesn’t talk much, but he doesn’t have to.//<portrait=normal>His craftsmanship speaks for him.
I’m a woodworker, but people tend to think of me as a general handyman, too.
That’s okay. I love to help out!
Ever tried a yoga class with <NPCName>Leah</>? I love it! She’s a wonderful instructor.
You should join us in class sometime, <PlayerName>$player</>! You’d love it.
I’ve been learning so much about marine life ever since my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved in with us.
Like, did you know octopuses have three hearts? Fascinating stuff!
When my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved to town, I invited him to come live with us right away.
He was hesitant at first, but I wouldn’t take no for an answer! He’s family.
He’s also a great addition to family board game night. So, win-win!
If <NPCName>Kira</> looks intimidating, it’s because she is.
Don’t let her prickly demeanor fool you, though. She’s a good person at heart.
I love the smell of sawdust in the morning!
You’re not really in a talking mood today, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I can tell. I have a sixth sense about these things.
I’ll tell you the same thing I tell my son, <NPCName>Archie</>: Measure twice, cut once.
Like it? I made it up myself!
Work is really picking up! I wonder if I’ll need to expand…
My favorite day of the year is Beach Cleanup Day. Coral Island is beautiful, but it takes work to keep it that way!
You’re coming this year, right?
Do you know <NPCName>Bree</> from the vineyard yet? I heard she used to be a model.
She still is, of course.//<portrait=happy>A model citizen, that is!
I saw a wonderfully crafted bannister at the vineyard the other day.//A rich mahogany, exquisite inlays, beautiful curves.
I’m a man who appreciates a fine bannister.
Did you know there are over seventeen species of trees growing on Coral Island?//<portrait=happy>Well, now you do!
Have you met <NPCName>Zarah</> yet? She’s very mysterious, always coming and going!
Y’know, it’s not just wood that I work with. I also carve a mean jack-o’-lantern.
I’ve never been diving in the ocean before, but my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, goes all the time. He tells me it’s beautiful down there.
I really need to find the time someday.
My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, has been pretending to be a squirrel for the past few weeks.
He’s actually very convincing. The only problem is I keep finding nuts hidden around the house.//<portrait=normal>He sure loves animal...that one.
<NPCName>Surya</> said there are whales not too far from here! I’d love to see them one day.
I used to make fanciful, artisan pieces.//<portrait=happy>Bookshelves with intricate scrollwork on them or hand-made jigsaw puzzles.
Now I mostly make utilitarian pieces. Desks, tables, chairs. No frills, just practical.
I enjoy those too, but sometimes I miss the old days.
I’m getting into chess! I started playing with <NPCName>Yuri</> at the Shack, and it’s really grown on me.
I might make her a custom chessboard as a thank-you. Don’t tell her, though. I want it to be a surprise!
I’d love to teach <NPCName>Archie</> more about woodworking.//But he seems to want to be a vet when he grows up, which is fine by me.//He should follow his heart.
I’m feeling a little under the weather today…
Whenever I start feeling sick, <NPCName>Dinda</> makes me tea with fresh peppermint from her garden.//It peps me right up!
I’m thinking of hiring <NPCName>Macy</> to take a family portrait.//<portrait=normal>She’s an excellent photographer!
How’s the soil today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Nutrient rich, I hope!
I saw <NPCName>Jack</> in yoga class last week!//He’s surprisingly flexible.
What you heard is true.<NPCName>Kira</> doesn't celebrate birthdays.//I think <NPCName>Kenny</> does though.
No, I don't know when <NPCName>Kenny</>'s birthday is. Sorry!
I’m thinking about taking up calligraphy. You know, with all my spare time…
<NPCName>Theo</> is one of the most positive people I know. I’m not sure how he does it, given…
Well, it doesn’t matter. He’s a remarkable person.
My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, is a huge animal lover. He’s always watching the animal channel on TV, learning all sorts of interesting facts.
<NPCName>Archie</> gets <NPCName>Dinda</>'s empathetic personality, that's for sure.//He would make a great vet.//Umm...nope.//<portrait=happy>He WILL make a great vet.
I almost sawed through my wallet in my workshop earlier today!//That’s never happened before.
I saw <NPCName>Jim</> doing some kind of martial arts thing at the beach the other day.//Karate, maybe. It was interesting!
I was going to ask him about it, but it looked like he wanted to be left alone.
<NPCName>Dinda</> surprised me with a beautiful bouquet of wooden flowers the other day.//<portrait=normal>She made them herself!
I don’t know how she found the time to make them without me knowing.//She’s so sweet! And sneaky!
We just harvested some fresh herbs from <NPCName>Dinda</>'s garden!
Let me tell ya, there’s nothing like fresh produce.
But look who I’m talking to! I don’t need to tell you that, do I?
Have you checked out the Fall colors yet?
I love this time of year. The air is crisp; the leaves put on a beautiful show…
And when the leaves fall off, you can really see how much yield a tree will give. It’s gorgeous!
There’s nothing better than sitting with a cup of hot cocoa while looking at the snow.
I love watching the snow fall!//<portrait=concerned>From inside, of course…
I’ve been racking my brain, trying to think of what to get <NPCName>Dinda</> for her birthday.
Oh, it’s not for months yet. But I’m terrible at coming up with gift ideas. This year, I want to be prepared!
The Harvest Festival is just around the corner!
Hot enough for ya? 'Cos it sure is for me.
There are simple crafts that you can make yourself to improve your farm, like scarecrows or lamp posts.
We sell some of these blueprints if you would like to try it.
I might go to the forest tomorrow and get some more woods.
We are making some new furniture.
I thought I'll stretch a bit here.
The house is not bad, eh? <NpcName>Dinda</> and I built it ourselves. Took us a long time, but it’s really sturdy!//We never thought we needed to expand because we were too caught up in work.
We used to live in the shed...it's now the little workshop right behind the shop counter, until we wanted to expand our family.//Then, we reconstructed the shed to build the extra bedrooms.
I don’t think I will go back to work today. I will just relax and see my friends.
Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.
Joining me to fish here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I’m sure that <NpcName>Rafael</> and <NpcName>Pablo</> are the only blacksmiths around here. They are the only ones who have the equipment to upgrade tools.
It’s probably not the worst idea to carry around a sword or something when you go to the cavern.
I think this place should have a trivia night. Don’t you?
I like teaching <NPCName>Archie</> fishing.//It's a good skill to have.
It’s so quiet here. So peaceful...one of my favorite place for sure.
Hardwood is great to work with. I find a ton down in the deep forest.
I really should reorganize my workshop. But I’m always just so busy…
You can hear the wind whistling through the trees from here.
When I walked into the workshop this morning, there was this amazing sunbeam streaming through the window.
The way it caught yesterday’s sawdust floating through the air was just… It was just magical.
I must have watched it for fifteen minutes.
<NPCName>Surya</> loves working with <NPCName>Ling</> down at the lab.
Wow! You're out and about!//I think I will stay indoors today because you know...the rain.
Need anything, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I don’t mind working in the rain if I already have a project to do.
It’s nice to rain like this sometimes. It cleans the neighborhood's drainage system.
We are not accepting projects right now, but if you need an upgrade or buy anything, stop by tomorrow.
I don’t have any project to do today, so I think I will stay indoors and avoid the storm.
Need anything, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I don’t mind working in the rain if I already have a project to do.
It’s nice to rain like this sometimes. It cleans the neighborhood's drainage system.
I don’t mind the snow if I already have a project to do.
Our herb plants wilted. None of them can survive the Winter snow.
I don’t mind the snow if I already have a project to do.
Our herb plants wilted. None of them can survive the Winter snow.
I love the rain. But not as much as you, I bet!
There’s nothing like the sound of rain pitter-pattering over the workshop. I could listen to it all day!
I hope we get some rain soon.
I love curling up with a good book on a rainy day. Don’t you?
What a perfect day to curl up with a good book!
